<p>I am trying to send a mail using MIME::Lite::TT::HTML.</p>  <p>This is my perl script.</p>  <pre><code>#!/usr/bin/perl use cPanelUserConfig;   use strict;  use warnings;  use MIME::Lite::TT::HTML;   my %params;   $params{first_name} = 'Frank';  $params{last_name}  = 'Wiles';  $params{amt_due}    = '24.99';   my %options;  $options{INCLUDE_PATH} = '.';   my $msg = MIME::Lite::TT::HTML-&gt;new(             From        =&gt;  'cs@pzr.com',             To          =&gt;  'xyz@gmail.com',             Subject     =&gt;  'Your new password',             Template    =&gt; { html =&gt; 'test.html.tt' },             TmplOptions =&gt;  \%options,             TmplParams  =&gt;  \%params,  );   $msg-&gt;send; </code></pre>  <p>I also created a file named test.html.tt in same directory. Content of that is:</p>  <pre><code>     &lt;html&gt;  &lt;body&gt;   &lt;strong&gt;Hi [% first_name %]&lt;/strong&gt;,   &lt;p&gt;  This is to confirm your purchase of $ [% amt_due %].  &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;  Thank you!  &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/body&gt;  &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But while executing script i am seeing this error:</p>  <p>[Wed Sep 30 11:09:06.557523 2015] [cgi:error] [pid 40187:tid 140571450533632] [client 123.136.217.67:49857] AH01215: file error - test.html.tt: not found: /home//public_html/orders/cgi-bin/testmail.pl</p>  <p>How to solve this?</p>